org.usfirst.frc.team69.util.oi

Class BadOIMapException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • org.usfirst.frc.team69.util.oi.BadOIMapException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class BadOIMapException
extends java.lang.Exception
    This exception is thrown when the class passed as a map to OI is invalid. This should only be thrown inside the RobotInspector program. If an invalid configuration is detected at runtime, we report an error to the dashboard and ignore the invalid part.
